description.S1: Anton's research sounds like it'd be valuable to Gladys.

blurb.B1: Leave town and go to Roseway Garden.
blurb.B2: You'll be attacked by a group of Raptidons as you approach Auntie-Biotics Lab 0013
blurb.B3: Then make your way southeast towards the Cover Lab.
blurb.B4: Inside you'll need to speak with Cassandra O'Malley.
blurb.B5: You can kill her or make a deal with her,
blurb.B6: but she has Auntie Cleo's Research Data.

O6.summary: Return to Gladys on the Groundbreaker

description.S1: You've acquired one of the company secrets that Gladys was talking about. You can return to her to sell it, or keep searching for more secrets.

blurb.B1: You can complete this quest by giving Gladys all or none of the secrets,
blurb.B2: though if you are going to give her one the best one to do is the toothpaste because it will cause you to complete The Doom That Came to Roseway.
blurb.B3: Whereas, either of the other two will Botch their Quests and you will gain no XP, only Bit Cartridges

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Oh good. You're not shooting at me. That's a start.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: It's been a bit of a day, so I'll get to the point. Yes, I have Crane's research. No, I'm not giving it back. Sorry to disappoint you.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Anton wants a problem fixed. I imagine he means you.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: You've got the wrong idea about me.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Yes, I imagine he does. But we all have problems - it is the human condition. I am myself ensnared in this wretched place.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: You want to kill me. I don't want to die. Therefore, it is in my best interest to negotiate with you. Help me get out of here, and I will pay you for my life.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Tell me what you need.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: We're not friends. If you expect me to help you, I expect you to hand over that research.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Why are you down here?

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: You're going to have to make me a better offer.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: <Attack> Or I could just shoot you and skip all the hassle.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: The first thing I need is a keycard to unlock my door. Then I'd need you to clear me a path out of here.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: There are two ways out. The quickest is through the front door, but Cleo security's bottled up in there. If you don't want to shoot them, I suppose you could talk to them.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: The other way out is through the loading bay, but you'd have to clear out the rapts for me. Then I could just slip out the back, sight unseen.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: All right. I'll help you out.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I'm not about to run errands for some pompous bandit.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I'm going to need a good reason to risk my neck for you.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Forget it. I'm not helping you.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: You might be the first stroke of luck I've had all day. Thank you. I'm in your debt.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Outstanding. I knew you would come around.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Don't flatter yourself. I expect you to pay me for my trouble.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: This doesn't make us friends.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Sit tight.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: On my honor, you will be well-rewarded.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: I do not have friends. I have associates.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Take your time. I am, to my chagrin, not going anywhere.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: You and I are on the same side. We both possess the means to fight back against a tyrannical and oppressive corporate regime.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: You aren't going to be fighting much of anything stuck down here.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: The corporate regime has been generous to freelancers like me.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I'm through talking.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: We are all of us trapped. You, me, the scientists. This is not a colony. It is a slave camp.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Yes. We raided the lab. Shot some guards. Killed a few scientists in the crossfire. But it was all for a higher cause.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: So you're a murderer with a conscience.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: The corporations don't care about the cause. Whatever you tear down, they can rebuild.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I'm done talking to you.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: All wars have casualties. I regret taking a life, but we were doing them a mercy. Better to die than live in a state of slavery.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: You're pretty conceited for a common bandit.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: I prefer "freedom fighter," but I will not quibble over semantics.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Come on now. Do you want to be dull and boring and servile like everyone else? Or do you want to break some rules?

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Then we will tear it down again. Do you know what propaganda by the deed means? It means we set an example by our actions. It means we send a message.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: What makes you think anyone's going to listen to your message?

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Because it is fun. You have not lived until you have taken a hammer to the establishment.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Come on now. Do you want to be dull and boring and servile like everyone else? Or do you want to break some rules?

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Think it over. I am not going anywhere. Which is, I suppose, rather the point.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Then you are nothing more than a hired gun. No better than an inanimate object, with no will or spirit of your own.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Being a hired gun is good work. It's always a seller's market.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: And you're just a two-bit bandit who likes to put on airs.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Say what you please. So long as you are on the establishment's payroll, you are nothing more than a confederate to tyranny.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I'm not about to be lectured on morality by some jumped-up bandit.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: At least I'm not trapped in an underground lab because I botched a raid.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: You're asking a great deal from me. This research is my only bargaining chip.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Then I suggest you hurry up and make your case.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: You need my help more than I need yours.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: You're in no position to bargain.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: You're not wrong. Help me get out of here, and I might be willing to hand over my research.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Same reason you are, more than likely. I imagine we picked up the same tip. Secret research facility, abandoned town, minimal security?

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: No, I'm tracking down a distress call.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Doesn't look minimal security to me. Or abandoned.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I'm not a bandit like you.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Crane actually sent out a cry for help? Oh, the poor bastard, seeing his life's work snatched from him. It must be like losing a child.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: No, but it is a secret. Well-hidden. Off the map. Any place worth hiding is worth raiding.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Granted, diet toothpaste is not exactly what comes to mind when I imagine secret research and underground labs.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Nothing wrong with taking care of your teeth.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I'm done listening to this. You're on your own.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Diet toothpaste. Can you imagine a more pernicious example of corporate materialism? I do not know what is worse - working here or dying here.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: So you went through all this trouble to steal a formula for ... diet toothpaste.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I'm glad you're finding time for soul-searching, what with being moments away from death.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I imagine you're about to find out. Goodbye.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: What matters is that I have been lied to. I was led to believe this was a high-priority corporate facility hiding valuable research.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: This job was not supposed to end with me stuck in some wretched lab, smelling like rapts. So I would be very much obliged if you gave me a break.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: What's in it for me?

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: Forget it. You're on your own.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: You mean other than the satisfaction of doing me a good turn? Trust me - I'll make it worth your while.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I don't know. My while is worth a lot.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: I am good for my word! You will be equitably rewarded, on my honor. But I will not haggle or bargain with you until you help me.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: And I am glad you have the luxury of sarcasm, whereas I have been made to spend my day listening to my crew die to corporate guns and hungry rapts.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Oh, please. I'm not shaking down valuables from hapless travelers. I'm stealing corporate secrets.

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: What kind of secrets are we talking?

dialog.speaker: Player
dialog.utterance: I'm not interested in helping you.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: This is an underground lab. Off the radar. That means their research is secret, and secrets are always valuable.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: I suppose it does not matter. Either Crane sent you, or you are some scavenger come to rob me in my moment of weakness.

dialog.speaker: CassandraOMalley (Female)
dialog.utterance: Let's make a deal. I'd like to go on living. You'd probably like to make some money. Help me get out of here, and I will pay you for your trouble.
